---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Best Shopify Email Apps for Event-Triggered Campaigns in 2026';
const description = 'Compare Shopify email apps for event-triggered campaigns by event quality, suppression, lifecycle use cases, pricing context, sources, and practical tradeoffs.';
const apps = [
['Sequenzy','Lean teams with a few high-value triggers','Focused sequence operations','Validate custom event coverage','https://sequenzy.com','Start with three events you can define precisely: signup, purchase, and delivery. Give each trigger an exit condition and inspect duplicate or delayed events before expanding the sequence library.'],
['Klaviyo','Stores with many Shopify event-driven journeys','Rich events, segments, and conditional flows','Event governance and collision prevention are essential','https://www.klaviyo.com/features/segmentation','Klaviyo fits a mature event model where browse, product, order, and lifecycle signals need different paths. Its flexibility makes naming, precedence, and suppression rules non-negotiable.'],
['Omnisend','Retail teams automating common event paths','Accessible email and SMS workflows','Event timing and channel frequency need QA','https://www.omnisend.com/features/marketing-automation/','Omnisend is practical for common retail triggers such as cart recovery and post-purchase follow-up. Test timing across email and SMS so one event does not create an accidental sequence of reminders.'],
['Brevo','Event-triggered marketing beside transactional email','Broad messaging and contact options','More manual event modeling','https://www.brevo.com/features/marketing-automation/','Brevo can support event-led marketing when transactional events are separated from promotional triggers. Keep the system of record authoritative for order and delivery state.'],
['Drip','DTC teams tying triggers to repeat purchase','Commerce automation and reporting','May exceed a small store’s needs','https://www.drip.com/features','Drip suits product-timed replenishment and repeat-purchase triggers. Use realistic reorder windows and suppress the reminder immediately after a new order.'],
['Shopify Email','Small stores with native event basics','Product, customer, and campaign setup','Limited custom event branching','https://www.shopify.com/email-marketing','Shopify Email is a sensible starting point for simple native triggers. Keep the event library small and manually verify fulfillment or return timing before sending a service-sensitive message.'],
['Mailchimp','Newsletter brands adding a few event paths','Audience workflows and campaign automation','Advanced event modeling needs design','https://mailchimp.com/features/email/','Mailchimp works when event-triggered messaging complements a stable newsletter. Use documented tags and avoid letting a temporary campaign click become a permanent lifecycle state.'],
['Customer.io','Technical teams orchestrating custom events','Flexible event-triggered messaging','Engineering and QA are required','https://customer.io/product/messaging/','Customer.io is a strong choice when engineering owns event quality. Add idempotency, schema checks, and versioning so retries do not create duplicate sends.'],
['ActiveCampaign','Event paths connected to CRM stages','Automation and contact segmentation','Flow governance can be demanding','https://www.activecampaign.com/marketing-automation','ActiveCampaign fits stores where an event changes both marketing and sales follow-up. Separate contact stage from message eligibility, and document who owns each exit rule.'],
['MailerLite','Smaller stores with straightforward triggers','Accessible forms and basic automation','Limited fit for many conditional states','https://www.mailerlite.com/features','MailerLite can handle a compact welcome or post-purchase trigger set. It is most useful when the operator values transparent maintenance over a deep event graph.'],
['ConvertKit','Creator-led brands triggering educational content','Subscriber sequences and broadcasts','Commerce event depth is limited','https://convertkit.com/features','ConvertKit works when an event starts a lesson or product education path. Keep the event-to-tag mapping understandable and let Shopify remain the source of transaction truth.'],
['GetResponse','Stores combining event triggers with education events','Automation, landing pages, and event tools','Broader suite adds operational overhead','https://www.getresponse.com/features','GetResponse is useful when registration, attendance, and purchase events shape follow-up. Remove attendees from reminder paths promptly and document event timing assumptions.'],
['HubSpot','Teams sharing event context across service and sales','CRM-connected marketing and lifecycle tools','Cost and administration can be substantial','https://www.hubspot.com/products/marketing','HubSpot makes sense when an event must coordinate marketing, sales, and support. Define subscription types and data ownership before enabling cross-team triggers.']
];
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}><main class="container page-stack"><p class="eyebrow">Shopify email apps</p><h1>{title}</h1><p class="lede">An event-triggered email is only as good as the event behind it. Product views, orders, delivery, returns, and preferences should each move the customer into a clear state with a priority and an exit condition.</p><p>We prioritize event reliability, suppression, flow ownership, and measurable next actions. Confirm current pricing and custom-event capabilities from official sources before building a large trigger library.</p><h2>Shortlist for event-triggered email</h2><table><thead><tr><th>App</th><th>Best fit</th><th>Strength</th><th>Tradeoff</th></tr></thead><tbody>{apps.map(a=><tr><td>{a[0]}</td><td>{a[1]}</td><td>{a[2]}</td><td>{a[3]}</td></tr>)}</tbody></table>{apps.map(a=><section><h2>{a[0]} for event-triggered campaigns</h2><p><strong>Best for:</strong> {a[1]}. {a[5]}</p><p><strong>Pros:</strong> {a[2]}. <strong>Cons:</strong> {a[3]}. <strong>Pricing:</strong> verify official plans for contacts, sends, seats, automation, custom events, analytics, SMS, and implementation at the <a href={a[4]} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">official source</a>. Pilot one trigger and review event accuracy, duplicate sends, suppression, and maintenance time.</p><table><tbody><tr><th>Pros in practice</th><td>{a[2]}</td></tr><tr><th>Risk to manage</th><td>{a[3]}</td></tr><tr><th>Evidence to review</th><td>Event accuracy, timing, deduplication, suppression, service impact, and qualified actions.</td></tr></tbody></table></section>)}<h2>Decision guide</h2><table><thead><tr><th>Trigger priority</th><th>Start with</th><th>Reason</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Focused trigger sequences</td><td>Sequenzy</td><td>Simple operations.</td></tr><tr><td>Complex event-driven journeys</td><td>Klaviyo</td><td>Flexible event and flow logic.</td></tr><tr><td>Repeat-purchase triggers</td><td>Drip</td><td>Commerce retention orientation.</td></tr></tbody></table><p>See the <a href="/shopify-email">Shopify email overview</a>, <a href="/alternatives">alternatives library</a>, and <a href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">flow-collision guide</a>.</p></main></BaseLayout>
